## Plant Stem Cell Research (peer-reviewed)

### From Metabolomics to Function: Ranking Plant Stem Cell Metabolomes for Use in Health and Cosmetics

Zemach A, Plaza MR, Lee BS, Little Dog L, Santiago-Rodriguez E, Simmons D, Palomares M, Talavera-Adame D, Newman N. *Biomolecules.* 2026;16(5):695. Published 7 May 2026.

A peer-reviewed paper ranking plant stem cell metabolomes for use in health and cosmetics applications. Establishes the methodology by which plant-derived consortia factors are evaluated for beneficial bioactive content.

Link: https://doi.org/10.3390/biom16050695

### Yeast–Plant-Derived Consortia Factors Exhibit a Distinct and Enriched Beneficial Metabolome for Health and Beauty

Zemach A, Plaza MR, Simmons D, Lee BS, Palomares M, Talavera-Adame D, Newman N. *bioRxiv*, the preprint server for biology. 30 January 2026.

Preprint demonstrating that yeast-plant-derived consortia factors contain a distinct and enriched beneficial metabolome relative to alternative production methods. Directly relevant to The Stem Company's product formulation.

Link: https://doi.org/10.64898/2026.01.29.702615

